    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends 👋, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To make mui list with alternate colors in react js, you can use . It will make mui list with alternate colors in React JS…","html":"<p>Hi Friends 👋,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To make mui list with alternate colors in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">className={index % 2 === 0 ? classes.evenItem : classes.oddItem}</code>. It will make mui list with alternate colors in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How to make mui list with alternate colors in react js</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages mui list in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI list.</li>\n<li>Use the list Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI list.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> List <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material/List'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ListItem <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material/ListItem'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> makeStyles <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/styles'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the list Component.</h3>\n<p>Lists are a continuous group of text or images. They are composed of items containing primary and supplemental actions, which are represented by icons and text.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>List<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">item<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> index</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ListItem\n      key<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>index<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>index <span class=\"token operator\">%</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span> <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span> <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> classes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>evenItem <span class=\"token operator\">:</span> classes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>oddItem<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      Item <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>item<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n   <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>ListItem<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>List<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material make mui list with alternate colors example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">list</code> Component. Then, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">className={index % 2 === 0 ? classes.evenItem : classes.oddItem}</code>. Then it will make mui list with alternate colors in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> List <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material/List'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ListItem <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material/ListItem'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> makeStyles <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/styles'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> useStyles <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">makeStyles</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">theme</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">evenItem</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">backgroundColor</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'#c6b7ed'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">oddItem</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">backgroundColor</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'#d1a2d1'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">AlternateColorList</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> classes <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useStyles</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>List<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">item<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> index</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ListItem\n          key<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>index<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n          className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>index <span class=\"token operator\">%</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span> <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span> <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> classes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>evenItem <span class=\"token operator\">:</span> classes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>oddItem<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          Item <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>item<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>ListItem<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>List<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> AlternateColorList<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and make mui list with alternate colors in react js.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/ec897/list-with-alternate-colors.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.78481012658228%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlYAAABXRUJQVlA4IEoAAADQAwCdASoUAAUAPtFapkuoJaOhsAgBABoJZQCdEf/gPIBXJLY2HAAA/pGzmZgR3CMOQeBKjkBAgOE9P77BQIDsVJmVFmPkrgAAAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, list, with, alternate, colors\"\n        title=\"React, list, with, alternate, colors\"\n        src=\"/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/8aab1/list-with-alternate-colors.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/81b7c/list-with-alternate-colors.webp 158w,\n/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/6ea66/list-with-alternate-colors.webp 315w,\n/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/8aab1/list-with-alternate-colors.webp 630w,\n/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/a70f5/list-with-alternate-colors.webp 945w,\n/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/4ef06/list-with-alternate-colors.webp 1260w,\n/static/9a912131415c0af2f4238f58f93be187/ec897/list-with-alternate-colors.webp 1366w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best 👍</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui list with alternate colors in react js?","tags":["React"],"date